  "Broker Comment" : "NON DECEMBER 13, 1976, JOHN W. SWEET, JR. WAS CHARGED WITH BANK THEFT OF LESS THAN $100 WHILE WITH THE COMMUNITY SAVINGS BANK AS A BANK OFFICER IN ROCHESTER, NY. SWEET IMPROPERLY REMOVED A \"HOLD\" ON A PERSONAL SAVINGS ACCOUNT LINKED TO A PERSONAL MORTGAGE.  THE SAVINGS ACCOUNT WAS TO BE MAINTAINED AT 125% OF THE OUTSTANDING LOAN.  SWEET WITHDREW $400 FROM THE ACCOUNT WITH 25% OF THE AMOUNT ($100) REPRESENTING THE BANK'S FUNDS.  ON JANUARY 10, 1977, SWEET ENTERED A PLEA OF NOLO CONTENDERE AND WAS CONVICTED OF THE CHARGE.  SWEET WAS GIVEN A SUSPENDED SENTENCE OF ONE YEAR BUT PLACED ON A ONE YEAR PROBATION PERIOD.  RESTITUTION HAD ALREADY BEEN MADE PRIOR TO THE SENTENCING.  THE JUDGEMENT WAS SIGNED BY HAROLD P. BURKE, U.S. DISTRICT JUDGE."
